<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 12:35:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>基于钙钛矿忆阻器和镍单原子工程还原氧化石墨烯阴极的反馈神经元</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/feedback-neurons-based-on-perovskite-memristor-with-nickel-single-atom-engineered-reduced-graphene-oxide-cathode</link><description>长期以来，科学家们一直将人类大脑视为计算的终极蓝图，寻求构建“神经形态”系统，以与我们自己的神经元相同的效率和灵活性处理信息。然而，事实证明，使用标准硬件来复制大脑激发和抑制信号的复杂能力（本质上是同时“说”和“听”）是很困难的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/feedback-neurons-based-on-perovskite-memristor-with-nickel-single-atom-engineered-reduced-graphene-oxide-cathode.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 12:35:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/feedback-neurons-based-on-perovskite-memristor-with-nickel-single-atom-engineered-reduced-graphene-oxide-cathode</guid></item><item><title>1903年诺贝尔物理学奖</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nobel-prize-in-physics-1903</link><description>1903 年诺贝尔物理学奖被平分，一半授予安东尼·亨利·贝克勒尔，“以表彰他在发现自发放射性方面所做出的杰出贡献”，另一半共同授予皮埃尔·居里和玛丽·居里（娘家姓斯科沃多夫斯卡），“以表彰他们在共同研究亨利·贝克勒尔教授发现的辐射现象时所做出的杰出贡献”&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nobel-prize-in-physics-1903.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 12:20:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nobel-prize-in-physics-1903</guid></item><item><title>饮食限制如何重新连接免疫力以防止感染</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/how-dietary-restriction-rewires-immunity-to-protect-against-infection</link><description>为了了解稀缺期间免疫反应中涉及的复杂相互作用，研究小组让小鼠接受 50% 的热量限制饮食，然后将它们暴露在感染肠道的细菌中。喂食标准饮食的小鼠经历了代谢崩溃——它们的血糖水平和体重直线下降。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-dietary-restriction-rewires-immunity-to-protect-against-infection2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 12:05:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/how-dietary-restriction-rewires-immunity-to-protect-against-infection</guid></item><item><title>原子薄反铁磁体中的六态时钟物理</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/six-state-clock-physics-in-an-atomically-thin-antiferromagnet</link><description>单层 NiPS3 的非线性光学微偏振法和原子蒙特卡罗模拟证明了 Berezinskii-Kosterlitz-Thouless 相，随着温度的降低，它让位于与六态时钟模型一致的长程有序。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/six-state-clock-physics-in-an-atomically-thin-antiferromagnet.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 11:50:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/six-state-clock-physics-in-an-atomically-thin-antiferromagnet</guid></item><item><title>数据中心可以在玻璃中存储信息数千年</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/data-centres-could-store-information-in-glass-for-thousands-of-years</link><description>微软研究人员开发了一种用激光将数据写入玻璃的技术，提高了充满数据的玻璃平板的机器人图书馆的前景&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/data-centres-could-store-information-in-glass-for-thousands-of-years.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 11:35:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/data-centres-could-store-information-in-glass-for-thousands-of-years</guid></item><item><title>PARP7 的 NAD+ 传感调节脂肪生成过程中 C/EBPβ 依赖性转录程序</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nad-sensing-by-parp7-regulates-the-c-ebp%ce%b2-dependent-transcription-program-during-adipogenesis</link><description>斯托克斯等人。证明 PARP7 在早期脂肪形成分化过程中通过 ADP-核糖基化-泛素-蛋白酶体途径“感知”核 NAD+ 水平，通过 p300 介导的 H3K27 乙酰化调节 C/EBPβ 依赖性促脂肪形成基因表达。稳定的 PARP7 促进 C/EBPβ 与全基因组染色质的结合，增强体内脂质合成和脂肪形成。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nad-sensing-by-parp7-regulates-the-c-ebpceb2-dependent-transcription-program-during-adipogenesis3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 11:20:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/nad-sensing-by-parp7-regulates-the-c-ebp%ce%b2-dependent-transcription-program-during-adipogenesis</guid></item><item><title>MEK-ERK 信号传导通过 Nmnat2 转录调节在轴突存活中的神经元亚型特异性作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-neuron-subtype-specific-role-of-mek-erk-signaling-in-axon-survival-via-transcriptional-regulation-of-nmnat2</link><description>岳等人。找到亚型特异性调节&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-neuron-subtype-specific-role-of-mek-erk-signaling-in-axon-survival-via-transcriptional-regulation-of-nmnat22.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 11:05:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-neuron-subtype-specific-role-of-mek-erk-signaling-in-axon-survival-via-transcriptional-regulation-of-nmnat2</guid></item><item><title>确定削弱食管内壁的遗传缺陷！</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/genetic-defect-that-weakens-esophageal-lining-identified</link><description>但导致巴雷特食管发病的分子因素仍知之甚少。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/genetic-defect-that-weakens-esophageal-lining-identified2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 10:50:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/genetic-defect-that-weakens-esophageal-lining-identified</guid></item><item><title>头发丝宽度的 LED 最终可能取代激光</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/hair-width-leds-could-eventually-replace-lasers</link><description>不比人类头发丝宽的 LED 很快就能承担传统上由激光处理的工作，从在服务器机架内移动数据到为下一代显示器供电。加州大学圣巴巴拉分校博士生 Roark Chao 与人合着的新研究指出了一条切实可行的前进道路。该研究是&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hair-width-leds-could-eventually-replace-lasers2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 10:35:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/hair-width-leds-could-eventually-replace-lasers</guid></item><item><title>一种新型铝释放可持续且更便宜的催化剂</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-new-form-of-aluminum-unlocks-sustainable-and-cheaper-catalysts</link><description>伦敦国王学院的一个研究小组分离出了一种新形式的铝——一种储量丰富的金属，可以为常用的稀土金属提供一种更便宜、更可持续的替代品。化学系高级讲师克莱尔·贝克韦尔 (Clare Bakewell) 博士和她的实验室开发了高活性铝分子，能够分解坚韧的化学键。发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-new-form-of-aluminum-unlocks-sustainable-and-cheaper-catalysts2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 10:20:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-new-form-of-aluminum-unlocks-sustainable-and-cheaper-catalysts</guid></item></channel></rss>